The lingering mind/The lingering mind: alertness and readiness to meet the situation. (Zanshin)

Zanshin is a continuing state of alertness and readiness to meet the situation. To stretch our metaphor a little — when working with data it’s important to remain open to alternative explanations and to provide the best possible summary of our data.

  • Sub-setting data: sensitivity analysis for outliers (filter, group_by)
  • Summary tables to reveal patterns in data (use Simpson’s paradox as teaching example)
  • Facets in graphs; ggsave

Making new datasets with filter

Sometimes it’s useful to create copies or subsets of your data.

idealdiamonds <- diamonds %>% filter(cut=="Ideal")
